<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="116" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,152,432]" pageId="6" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,152,179]" pageId="6" pageNumber="116">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Forewing length: 
<quantity box="[532,593,153,179]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="116" unit="mm" value="6.0">6mm</quantity>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laszlo, Ronkay &amp; Witt" authorityYear="2010" box="[605,740,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Porcellanola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="langtangi">
<emphasis box="[605,740,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="116">P. langtangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described from Central 
<collectingCountry box="[1019,1086,153,179]" name="Nepal" pageId="6" pageNumber="116">Nepal</collectingCountry>
is very similar externally to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laszlo, Ronkay &amp; Witt" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Porcellanola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ayutthaya">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="116">P. ayutthaya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurring in North 
<collectingCountry box="[488,590,189,215]" name="Thailand" pageId="6" pageNumber="116">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, the two species are easily distinguishable by their surprisingly substantial differences in genitalia (
<bibRefCitation author="Laszlo, G. M. &amp; Ronkay, G. &amp; Witt, T. J." box="[425,635,225,251]" pageId="6" pageNumber="116" pagination="19 - 23" refId="ref3342" refString="Laszlo, G. M., Ronkay, G. &amp; Witt, T. J. (2010) Contribution to the Nolinae (Lepidoptera, Noctuidae) fauna of North Thailand. Esperiana, 15, 19 - 23." type="journal article" year="2010">
László 
<emphasis box="[509,559,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="116">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
). In Sikkim, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laszlo, Ronkay &amp; Witt" authorityYear="2010" box="[781,917,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Porcellanola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="langtangi">
<emphasis box="[781,917,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="116">P. langtangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs sympatrically with 
<taxonomicName authority="Joshi &amp; Singh &amp; László &amp; Kuni, 2020" authorityName="Joshi &amp; Singh &amp; László &amp; Kuni" authorityYear="2020" box="[1224,1338,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Porcellanola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sikkima" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1224,1338,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="116">P. sikkima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1346,1436,225,251]" pageId="6" pageNumber="116">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1346,1436,225,251]" pageId="6" pageNumber="116" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laszlo, Ronkay &amp; Witt" authorityYear="2006" box="[198,333,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Porcellanola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sukhothai">
<emphasis box="[198,333,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="116">P. sukhothai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but is unmistakable for both of them according to its conspicuously different forewing pattern split into a clear whitish basal and dark-colored apical half of forewing compared to the more variegated and complex wing pattern of the latter species. The detailed diagnoses of male and female genitalia of the related species are provided in detail in their original descriptions (
<bibRefCitation author="Laszlo, G. M. &amp; Ronkay, G. &amp; Witt, T. J." box="[687,892,369,395]" pageId="6" pageNumber="116" pagination="19 - 23" refId="ref3342" refString="Laszlo, G. M., Ronkay, G. &amp; Witt, T. J. (2010) Contribution to the Nolinae (Lepidoptera, Noctuidae) fauna of North Thailand. Esperiana, 15, 19 - 23." type="journal article" year="2010">
László 
<emphasis box="[770,819,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="116">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Laszlo, G. M. &amp; Ronkay, G. &amp; Witt, T. J." box="[903,1109,369,396]" pageId="6" pageNumber="116" pagination="265 - 276" refId="ref3290" refString="Laszlo, G. M., Ronkay, G. &amp; Witt, T. J. (2006) Description of a new genus and five new species of Nolinae from Thailand. Investigation on Asian Nolidae III. Entomofauna, 27 (21), 265 - 276." type="journal article" year="2006">
László 
<emphasis box="[985,1041,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="116">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
